entries.meaning: (computing, uncountable) A feature in wordprocessing whereby each typed character replaces the character after the cursor rather than being inserted before it.
(historical, countable) A kind of steam wagon having the engine above the cab.

verbs.description: overtype (third-person singular simple present overtypes, present participle overtyping, simple past and past participle overtyped)

entries.meaning: To type on top of something already typed.
examples: You can produce the yen sign ¥ by overtyping an equals sign = on a letter Y.
